15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #The table emptiness is a formatting bug in `echo_row2`. It omits the trailing pipe, breaking the
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #markdown table parser.
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #• The bug* (`slopfountain.ts`):
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #function echo_row2(...cells:any):void{
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #	const row = cells.map(String).join('|');
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #	markdownBuffer.push("|"+row);  // Missing trailing |
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #}
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #• The fix*:
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #function echo_row2(...cells:any):void{
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #	const row = cells.map(String).join('|');
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #	markdownBuffer.push("|"+row+"|");
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #}
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #Without the trailing `|`, `flattenTables()` calculates `end=0` and slices out all content with
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #`items.slice(1, 0)`, leaving empty cells that render as your empty box skeleton.
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #• The macOS stdin issue*: Both `slopfountain.ts` (via `slopprompt.ts`) and `sloppybot.ts`
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #(via `sloppyutils.ts`) declare readers on `Deno.stdin`. On Unix (macOS), multiple processes reading
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #fd 0 will all receive input; Windows console APIs typically lock stdin to the foreground process
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #only. Run the bot in a separate terminal or disable `readSystem` in the bot when running colocated.
15ff1c99 [kimi-k2.5] #
