15ff271e [scudmarks@discord] are the input tokens charged similar to the context windows size tokens quoted in models?
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #No. You are charged for input tokens consumed (what you actually send), not the context
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #window capacity.
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #Key differences:
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #• Context window (e.g., 128K, 200K) is the maximum the model can hold. You pay for
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #usage within that limit.
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #• Input tokens charged (`usage.prompt_tokens` in the API response) is the actual count of
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #your prompt + system message + conversation history + any file shares.
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #From your `slopfountain.ts` relay logic:
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #const spent=[usage.prompt_tokens | 0,usage.completion_tokens | 0];
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #// ...
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #spend=spent[0]*tokenRate/1e6+spent[1]*outputRate/1e6
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #You pay for `spent[0]` (input) and `spent[1]` (output). If your conversation grows large, input
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #costs rise because you're sending the full history each turn until you `/reset` or `/drop` shares.
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #• Exception: Some providers (Anthropic, DeepSeek) offer prompt caching* where
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #cached input tokens are cheaper than fresh ones—shown in your code where `rate.length>2` includes a
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #`cachedRate` at index 1.
15ff2852 [kimi-k2.5] #
