1609f5aa [scudmarks@discord] what produces the sound when laser cleaner sweeps across surface?
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #When a laser cleaner sweeps across a surface, the sound primarily comes from rapid thermal
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #expansion and explosive vaporization of contaminants and surface material.
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #Key mechanisms producing the acoustic signature:
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #• Thermal shock and ablation* – The high-energy laser pulses (typically nanosecond or
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #femtosecond duration) instantly heat absorbed contaminants to thousands of degrees Celsius, causing
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #them to vaporize or sublimate. This creates miniature explosions at the surface.
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #• Laser-induced plasma* – At sufficient energy densities, the vaporized material ionizes,
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #forming a rapidly expanding plasma plume. This expansion creates shock waves in the surrounding
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #air, producing the characteristic popping or crackling sound.
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #• Mechanical vibration* – The thermal stress induces rapid expansion and contraction in
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #both the contaminant layer and substrate, generating audible vibrations.
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #The specific acoustic signature varies with laser parameters: pulse duration, wavelength, fluence
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #(energy density), and the composition of what's being removed (rust, paint, oxides, or biological
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #material). Higher fluence produces louder, sharper reports as more material undergoes phase change
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #and plasma formation.
1609f743 [kimi-k2.5] #
