160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #For vintage 6800 Williams coin-ops (Defender, Robotron, Joust, Stargate—circa 1980–1984), the
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #ethical landscape favors preservation and archival research over strict copyright
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #adherence, provided the work is non-commercial and educational.
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #• Context matters:*
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #- Cultural heritage: These represent foundational digital artifacts. The 6800 assembly is a
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #dead language commercially; no revenue stream exists for the original ROMs as arcade software.
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #- Abandonment: Williams Electronics (now under Scientific Games/ Light & Wonder) hasn't
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #monetized these specific 6800 implementations in decades. The hardware is unobtainable except via
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #restoration.
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #- Creator intent: Eugene Jarvis and Larry DeMar have historically supported the
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #preservation community, recognizing that emulation and reverse engineering keep these mechanical
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #artworks alive.
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #• Ethical boundaries:*
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #- ✓ Archival: Decoding 6800 opcodes to understand collision detection algorithms or sound
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #synthesis (your LFSR discussion) serves historical documentation.
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #- ✓ Educational: Translating assembly to C pseudocode for academic study of real-time 6800
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #interrupt handling.
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #- ✗ Commercial: Selling reprogrammed ROMs or cloned hardware without licensing.
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #- ✗ Circumvention: Breaking modern encryption on current Williams/Bally slot machines
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #(active revenue products).
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #• The "gray": Technically, these ROMs remain under copyright until ~2075–2095 (corporate
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #authorship, 95-year term). However, ethical use aligns with fair use* principles:
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #transformative (analysis vs. consumption), non-commercial, and no market harm (the market for 1981
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #Defender ROMs is zero).
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #If your tooling produces high-level descriptions of audio algorithms or collision physics rather
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #than drop-in replacement code, it functions as digital archaeology—ethical and culturally
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #valuable.
160a482c [kimi-k2.5] #
