160a9c08 [kimi-k2.5] #<50mW    Class 3B, requires safety glasses
160a9c08 [kimi-k2.5] #1W+      Class 4, burns skin, ignites paper, instant retina damage from diffuse reflections
160a9c08 [kimi-k2.5] #
160a9c08 [kimi-k2.5] #
160a9c08 [kimi-k2.5] #For a home vector monitor, you want <100mW (ideally 50mW @ 445nm blue or 30mW @ 532nm
160a9c08 [kimi-k2.5] #green) with beam expansion to reduce intensity. A 1W unit requires:
160a9c08 [kimi-k2.5] #- Neutral density filters (OD 2.0 or 3.0) to attenuate to safe levels
160a9c08 [kimi-k2.5] #- Interlocked enclosure (opening the case kills power)
